-- Zimbabwe’s Mugabe to Miss ANC Centenary Event, Herald Says
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2012-01-07T09:08:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/zimbabwe-s-mugabe-to-miss-anc-centenary-event-herald-says.html
Zimbabwean President  Robert Mugabe 
will miss this weekend’s celebration of the centenary of  South
Africa ’s ruling  African National Congress  because he is on leave
in the  Far East , the state-owned  Herald  newspaper reported,
citing  George Charamba , Mugabe’s spokesman.  Mugabe’s deputy, Joice Mujuru, will represent him at the
event in Mangaung, in South Africa’s central Free State
Province, the Harare-based newspaper said. The ANC had
previously said Mugabe would attend.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 